Tour Eiffel.name: Eiffel Tower
Tour Eiffel.description: Landmark 330m-high 19th-century tower. Gustave Eiffel's iconic, wrought-iron 1889 tower, with steps and elevators to observation decks.

Colisee.name: Colosseum
Colisee.description: Monumental 3-tiered Roman amphitheater once used for gladiatorial games, with guided tour option.
Colisee.adresse: Piazza del Colosseo, 1, 00184 Roma RM, Italy

Acropole.name: Acropolis of Athens
Acropole.description: Ruins of iconic 5th-century B.C. temple complex on Athens' rocky hilltop undergoing restoration.

Masjid al-Haram.name: Masjid al-Haram
Masjid al-Haram.description: Massive mosque that is part of the Hajj. Part of the Hajj pilgrimage, this mosque is the largest in the world & holds up to 4 million people.

Fontaine de Trevi.name: Trevi Fountain
Fontaine de Trevi.description: Aqueduct-fed rococo fountain, designed by Nicola Salvi & completed in 1762, with sculpted figures.
Fontaine de Trevi.adresse: Piazza di Trevi, 00187 Roma RM, Italy

Porte de l'Inde.name: Gateway Of India Mumbai
Porte de l'Inde.description: Waterfront Indo-Saracenic triumphal arch. Grand, Indo-Saracenic-style, 26m-tall triumphal stone arch, built on the waterfront in 1924.
Porte de l'Inde.adresse: Apollo Bandar, Colaba, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400001, India

Place de la Constitution.name: Plaza de la Constitución
Place de la Constitution.description: Mexico City's main square has roots to the Aztecs & is now the site of frequent cultural events.
Place de la Constitution.adresse: P.za de la Constitución S/N, Centro Histórico de la Cdad. de México, Centro, Cuauhtémoc, 06010 Ciudad de México, CDMX, Mexico

Musée du Louvre.name: Louvre Museum
Musée du Louvre.description: Former historic palace housing huge art collection, from Roman sculptures to da Vinci's Mona Lisa.

Taj Mahal.name: Taj Mahal
Taj Mahal.description: 17th-century, Mughal-style, marble mausoleum with minarets, a mosque & famously symmetrical gardens.
Taj Mahal.adresse: Dharmapuri, Forest Colony, Tajganj, Agra, Uttar Pradesh 282001, India
